<p>Incidentally, donâ€™t let salary be a factor.  I just watched someone turn down one of these breakout companies because Microsoft offered him $30k per year more in salaryâ€”that was a terrible decision.  He will not build interesting things and may not work with smart people.  In a few years, when itâ€™s time for something new, the options in front of him will be much worse than they could have been.</p>
